724378f-a.title: Manhattan: West Broadway - Leonard Street
724378f-a.text:
West Broadway, west side, south from Leonard to Worth Street's, showing a row of low structures (No's. 186 to 170 inclusive) overshadowed by the 24-storied Western Union Building. The latter occupies the entire block to the south, Worth to Thomas Street's, west to Hudson. The side shown here is the Worth Street frontage. At the right margin is a garage bearing No. 24-32 Leonard Street.
July 12, 1939
P. L. Sperr
